// Sprint 9 Increment A — the D-345 array-indexer emission fix, end to end
// through the full pipeline: lex -> parse -> type-check -> compile -> VM.
// Before this increment, arr[i] compiled to nothing (no VisitIndex override)
// and crashed the VM with a stack underflow; this is the regression proof
// that a real .grob script indexing an array now runs correctly. Also
// exercises matrix[r][c] (D-112 multi-dimensional, chained index reads).

arr := [10, 20, 30]
print(arr[0])
print(arr[1])
print(arr[2])

matrix := [[1, 2], [3, 4]]
print(matrix[0][1])
print(matrix[1][0])
